      public void save​(java.lang.String projectName, java.lang.String date, int width, int height, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> imgList, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> xy, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> radii, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> labelString, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> labelXY)
      Creates a SaveData object. Calls the save method in the model class with the SaveData object and the name of the file that it will be saved as.
      Parameters:
      projectName - - name of garden project
      height - - height of garden
      width - - width of garden
      imgList - - ArrayList of paths of plant images
      xy - - ArrayList of x and y locations for plant images
      saveName - - file name that the file will be saved as
